{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bfc54c131ac8836f", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# NAVA: Native Audio-Visual Alignment for Generation\narXiv: 2605.30073\nAuthors: Longbin Ji∗\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose NAVA, a Native Audio-Visual Alignment framework that formulates joint audio-video generation as context-conditioned native audio-visual alignment to enable precise event-level correspondence modeling.\n  2. We introduce an Align-then-Fuse MMDiT architecture for modality-aware audio-video alignment and efficient collaborative denoising, alongside Timbre-in-Context Conditioning for flexible content-timbre binding.\n  3. Extensive experiments and user studies demonstrate that NAVA significantly outperforms representative baselines in audio-visual synchronization, semantic consistency, visual quality, and timbre controllability.\n\nTags: experiments, we propose, we introduce, extensive experiments", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "1718203d-6686-4b65-9f15-1ee9f4f04d8a", "uuid": "b7791a97-73ce-42f5-b08f-3c7df1341431", "timestamp": "2026-07-12T03:47:58.616Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# NAVA: Native Audio-Visual Alignment for Generation\narXiv: 2605.30073\nAuthors: Longbin Ji∗\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose NAVA, a Native Audio-Visual Alignment framework that formulates joint audio-video generation as context-conditioned native audio-visual alignment to enable precise event-level correspondence modeling.\n  2. We introduce an Align-then-Fuse MMDiT architecture for modality-aware audio-video alignment and efficient collaborative denoising, alongside Timbre-in-Context Conditioning for flexible content-timbre binding.\n  3. Extensive experiments and user studies demonstrate that NAVA significantly outperforms representative baselines in audio-visual synchronization, semantic consistency, visual quality, and timbre controllability.\n\nTags: experiments, we propose, we introduce, extensive experiments", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bf1d16b9f68b3527", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# MOVA: Towards Scalable and Synchronized Video-Audio Generation\narXiv: 2602.08794\nAuthors: \nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We develop MOVA, a synchronized video-audio generation model with an asymmetric dual-tower architecture that leverages pre-trained video and audio generation models.\n  2. We design a fine-grained audio-video captioning pipeline to produce high-quality bimodal training data at scale.\n  3. By scaling video-audio training, we achieve continuous improvements in synchronization performance across both modalities.\n\nTags: related-work, we develop, we design, by scaling", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "1718203d-6686-4b65-9f15-1ee9f4f04d8a", "uuid": "25febf73-b765-44f6-a08d-2ce4da55456d", "timestamp": "2026-07-12T03:47:58.833Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# MOVA: Towards Scalable and Synchronized Video-Audio Generation\narXiv: 2602.08794\nAuthors: \nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We develop MOVA, a synchronized video-audio generation model with an asymmetric dual-tower architecture that leverages pre-trained video and audio generation models.\n  2. We design a fine-grained audio-video captioning pipeline to produce high-quality bimodal training data at scale.\n  3. By scaling video-audio training, we achieve continuous improvements in synchronization performance across both modalities.\n\nTags: related-work, we develop, we design, by scaling", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
